## Implementation Plan

### Problem
- .github/release.yml commit_patterns lacked named capture groups (?<type>...)
  and (?<scope>...) needed for Craft's title stripping feature
- CI had an unnecessary merge job to combine artifacts into a single SHA-named
  artifact, which Craft 2.21.1+ no longer requires
- .craft.yml used the old separate-key changelog format

### Changes

#### .github/release.yml
- All commit_patterns now use (?<type>...) and (?<scope>...) named capture
  groups so Craft strips conventional commit prefixes from changelog entries
  (e.g. 'feat(api): add endpoint' becomes 'Add endpoint')
- Added Breaking Changes category (semver: major) from Craft defaults, matching
  any conventional commit with ! (e.g. feat!:, fix!:)
- Expanded Internal Changes patterns to include refactor|meta|perf from Craft
  defaults, merged with existing build|ref|chore|ci|tests?

#### .craft.yml
- Bumped minVersion from 2.17.0 to 2.21.1 (for workflow-scoped artifacts)
- Added artifactProvider config: fetches artifact-* from ci.yml workflow
- Modernized changelog from separate keys (changelog: CHANGELOG.md +
  changelogPolicy: auto) to object format (changelog: {filePath, policy})

#### .github/workflows/ci.yml
- Removed the merge job (combined artifact-build_lambda_layer and artifact-docs
  into a single SHA-named artifact) — Craft now pulls individual artifacts
- Removed compression-level: '0' from upload steps (was only needed for merging)

### References
- Craft title stripping docs: https://craft.sentry.dev/configuration/#title-stripping-default-behavior
- Craft artifact provider docs: https://craft.sentry.dev/configuration/#github-artifact-provider-configuration
